1. Policy Types (Policy Ke Types):

Term Assurance: Ye policy sirf death coverage deti hai, aur premium cheap hota hai. Businessmen ya mortgage 
repayment ke liye achha hai.

Endowment Assurance: Long-term endowment ab itna popular nahi, lekin short-term endowment (6-9 years) popular hai.

Investment Policy: 90%-95% premium invest hota hai, aur life cover milta hai. Ye policy 2-5 saal ki hoti hai.

Whole-Life Assurance: Ye policy ab popular nahi hai, kyunki agar aap survive kar jaate ho, to aapko kuch nahi milta.


2. Premium Factors (Premium Kaise Calculate Hota Hai):

Age: Jaise-jaise age badhegi, premium bhi badhega.

Health: Agar koi medical condition hai (e.g., diabetes), to premium zyada ho sakta hai.

Smoking: Smokers ko higher premium pay karna padta hai.

Occupation: Agar high-risk job hai, to premium zyada hoga.

Lifestyle: Hazardous hobbies (e.g., skydiving) bhi premium ko badhate hain.


3. Coverage Amount (Coverage Kitni Ho Sakti Hai):

Minimum: ₦100,000 se ₦500,000.

Maximum: ₦10 million se ₦50 million.

Adjustment: Coverage ko income ya occupation ke hisaab se adjust kiya ja sakta hai.


4. Nominee Requirements (Nominee Ki Information):

Information: Name, relationship, date of birth, contact details.

Multiple Nominees: Haan, multiple nominees add kar sakte hain aur unke liye percentage define kar sakte hain.

Age Restriction: Nominee ki age 18+ honi chahiye.


5. Policy Duration (Policy Duration Ka Impact):

Policy Term: 5, 10, 20, 30 saal tak ho sakti hai.

Premium Calculation: Longer duration mein premium kam hote hain, short-term mein zyada.

Renewal/Conversion: Policy ke end par renewal ya conversion ka option ho sakta hai.